-- Catroga Will Become EDP Chairman From February, Diario Reports
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-01-05T07:59:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/catroga-will-become-edp-chairman-from-february-diario-reports.html
Eduardo Catroga will become chairman
of Portuguese utility EDP-Energias de Portugal SA’s general and
supervisory board from February, Diario Economico reported,
without saying how it obtained the information.  Catroga will replace Antonio Almeida, who didn’t plan to
continue in the post, according to the Portuguese newspaper.  Antonio Mexia will remain as chief executive officer and
that appointment will be confirmed at an extraordinary
shareholder meeting that will take place in the first two weeks
of February, Diario said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  